{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":908,"text":"I'd like to talk about my dad."},{"time":2500,"text":"My dad has Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":5076,"text":"He started showing the symptoms about 12 years ago,"},{"time":8636,"text":"and he was officially diagnosed in 2005."},{"time":12023,"text":"Now he's really pretty sick. He needs help eating,"},{"time":16348,"text":"he needs help getting dressed, he doesn't really know where he is"},{"time":20236,"text":"or when it is, and it's been really, really hard."},{"time":24100,"text":"My dad was my hero and my mentor for most of my life,"},{"time":27612,"text":"and I've spent the last decade watching him disappear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31140,"text":"My dad's not alone. There's about 35 million people globally living with some kind of dementia,"},{"time":39277,"text":"and by 2030 they're expecting that to double to 70 million."},{"time":43926,"text":"That's a lot of people."},{"time":46076,"text":"Dementia scares us. The confused faces and shaky hands of people who have dementia,"},{"time":52692,"text":"the big numbers of people who get it, they frighten us."},{"time":56540,"text":"And because of that fear, we tend to do one of two things:"},{"time":60285,"text":"We go into denial: \"It's not me, it has nothing to do with me, it's never going to happen to me.\""},{"time":65740,"text":"Or, we decide that we're going to prevent dementia,"},{"time":69373,"text":"and it will never happen to us because we're going to do everything right and it won't come and get us."},{"time":74189,"text":"I'm looking for a third way: I'm preparing to get Alzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79940,"text":"Prevention is good, and I'm doing the things that you can do to prevent Alzheimer's."},{"time":85500,"text":"I'm eating right, I'm exercising every day, I'm keeping my mind active,"},{"time":90820,"text":"that's what the research says you should do."},{"time":93724,"text":"But the research also shows that there's nothing that will 100 percent protect you."},{"time":98212,"text":"If the monster wants you, the monster's gonna get you."},{"time":101724,"text":"That's what happened with my dad."},{"time":104164,"text":"My dad was a bilingual college professor. His hobbies were chess, bridge and writing op-eds."},{"time":110012,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":114018,"text":"He got dementia anyway."},{"time":116136,"text":"If the monster wants you, the monster's gonna get you."},{"time":118573,"text":"Especially if you're me, 'cause Alzheimer's tends to run in families."},{"time":124333,"text":"So I'm preparing to get Alzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128082,"text":"Based on what I've learned from taking care of my father,"},{"time":130036,"text":"and researching what it's like to live with dementia, I'm focusing on three things in my preparation:"},{"time":135284,"text":"I'm changing what I do for fun, I'm working to build my physical strength,"},{"time":141276,"text":"and -- this is the hard one -- I'm trying to become a better person."},{"time":148075,"text":"Let's start with the hobbies. When you get dementia, it gets harder and harder to enjoy yourself."},{"time":153764,"text":"You can't sit and have long talks with your old friends, because you don't know who they are."},{"time":157900,"text":"It's confusing to watch television, and often very frightening."},{"time":162188,"text":"And reading is just about impossible."},{"time":164812,"text":"When you care for someone with dementia, and you get training,"},{"time":168268,"text":"they train you to engage them in activities that are familiar, hands-on, open-ended."},{"time":173772,"text":"With my dad, that turned out to be letting him fill out forms."},{"time":178284,"text":"He was a college professor at a state school; he knows what paperwork looks like."},{"time":183789,"text":"He'll sign his name on every line, he'll check all the boxes,"},{"time":188444,"text":"he'll put numbers in where he thinks there should be numbers."},{"time":190819,"text":"But it got me thinking, what would my caregivers do with me?"},{"time":194812,"text":"I'm my father's daughter. I read, I write, I think about global health a lot."},{"time":200308,"text":"Would they give me academic journals so I could scribble in the margins?"},{"time":204564,"text":"Would they give me charts and graphs that I could color?"},{"time":207668,"text":"So I've been trying to learn to do things that are hands-on."},{"time":211868,"text":"I've always liked to draw, so I'm doing it more even though I'm really very bad at it."},{"time":217174,"text":"I am learning some basic origami. I can make a really great box."},{"time":222796,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":224943,"text":"And I'm teaching myself to knit, which so far I can knit a blob."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232025,"text":"But, you know, it doesn't matter if I'm actually good at it. What matters is that my hands know how to do it."},{"time":236668,"text":"Because the more things that are familiar, the more things my hands know how to do,"},{"time":240157,"text":"the more things that I can be happy and busy doing when my brain's not running the show anymore."},{"time":245150,"text":"They say that people who are engaged in activities are happier,"},{"time":249760,"text":"easier for their caregivers to look after, and it may even slow the progress of the disease."},{"time":254652,"text":"That all seems like win to me."},{"time":257164,"text":"I want to be as happy as I can for as long as I can."},{"time":260187,"text":"A lot of people don't know that Alzheimer's actually has physical symptoms,"},{"time":264708,"text":"as well as cognitive symptoms. You lose your sense of balance,"},{"time":268982,"text":"you get muscle tremors, and that tends to lead people to being less and less mobile."},{"time":274539,"text":"They get scared to walk around. They get scared to move."},{"time":277124,"text":"So I'm doing activities that will build my sense of balance."},{"time":280564,"text":"I'm doing yoga and tai chi to improve my balance, so that when I start to lose it,"},{"time":285225,"text":"I'll still be able to be mobile."},{"time":287207,"text":"I'm doing weight-bearing exercise, so that I have the muscle strength"},{"time":291149,"text":"so that when I start to wither, I have more time that I can still move around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295278,"text":"Finally, the third thing. I'm trying to become a better person."},{"time":300879,"text":"My dad was kind and loving before he had Alzheimer's, and he's kind and loving now."},{"time":305646,"text":"I've seen him lose his intellect, his sense of humor, his language skills,"},{"time":310526,"text":"but I've also seen this: He loves me, he loves my sons,"},{"time":315006,"text":"he loves my brother and my mom and his caregivers."},{"time":318717,"text":"And that love makes us want to be around him, even now."},{"time":323422,"text":"even when it's so hard."},{"time":324806,"text":"When you take away everything that he ever learned in this world,"},{"time":328109,"text":"his naked heart still shines."},{"time":330398,"text":"I was never as kind as my dad, and I was never as loving."},{"time":334317,"text":"And what I need now is to learn to be like that."},{"time":337365,"text":"I need a heart so pure that if it's stripped bare by dementia, it will survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342838,"text":"I don't want to get Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":345357,"text":"What I want is a cure in the next 20 years, soon enough to protect me."},{"time":349221,"text":"But if it comes for me, I'm going to be ready."},{"time":352671,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354421,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}